  <!-- ANSWER CAPSULE: How bail works in Garfield County -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: var(--slate-50);">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">How Does Bail Work in Garfield County, Oklahoma?</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Angel Bail Bonds provides 24/7 bail bond services for anyone arrested in Garfield County, Oklahoma. The Garfield County Detention Center at 1020 South 10th Street in Enid books inmates around the clock and has a capacity of 204 inmates. After bail is set, Angel Bail Bonds can post the bond and most defendants are released within 2 to 6 hours. We serve Garfield County from our Stillwater office, approximately 65 miles away.</strong></p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">When someone is arrested in Garfield County, they are transported to the Garfield County Detention Center in Enid for booking. The booking process includes identification verification, fingerprinting, a health screening, and entry of charges into the system. The detention center is managed by the Garfield County Sheriff's Office and operates as a medium-security facility established in 1931. Once booking is complete and bail has been set — either through the preset bond schedule or by a judge — a bail bond can be posted to secure release.</p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">Garfield County is one of the larger counties in north-central Oklahoma, with a 2020 Census population of 62,846. Enid alone accounts for over 51,000 residents. The county sees a higher volume of arrests than many surrounding rural counties, but Angel Bail Bonds has the experience and availability to handle bonds at the Garfield County Detention Center at any hour. For more serious offenses or felony charges where a judge must set bail, the process moves through the Garfield County Courthouse.</p>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Where Is the Garfield County Courthouse and When Are Arraignments?</h3>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>The Garfield County Courthouse is located at 114 West Broadway Avenue, Enid, OK 73701. The courthouse is open Monday through Friday, 8:00 AM to 4:30 PM. For arraignment schedules and docket information, contact the Court Clerk at (580) 237-0232 or check the Oklahoma State Courts Network at oscn.net for current docket calendars.</strong></p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">Garfield County falls within Oklahoma District 4 for court administration. If your loved one's bail requires a judge's approval, Angel Bail Bonds can coordinate with the court schedule to post the bond as quickly as possible after the arraignment hearing. We monitor Garfield County dockets regularly and can advise you on the expected timeline for your case.</p>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">How Do I Visit Someone in the Garfield County Detention Center?</h3>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-700); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;"><strong>Garfield County Detention Center visitation hours are Monday through Friday 7:30 AM to 9:00 PM and Saturday through Sunday 7:30 AM to 2:30 PM. The detention center is located at 1020 S 10th Street, Enid, OK 73701. Call (580) 548-2429 for current visitation policies. The facility uses Securus Technologies for inmate phone calls and video visitation.</strong></p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">Contact the detention center directly to confirm current visitation policies, as they can change based on facility conditions and staffing. If you need to check on an inmate's status or find out their bail amount, the Garfield County Sheriff's Office also provides inmate roster information. You can reach the Sheriff's Office at (580) 237-0244 for general inquiries.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT GARFIELD COUNTY -->
  <section style="padding: 48px 1.5rem; background: white;">
    <div style="max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;">
      <h2 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px;">About Garfield County, Oklahoma</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">Garfield County is located in north-central Oklahoma with a population of approximately 62,846 residents as of the 2020 Census. The county seat is Enid, the largest city in northwest Oklahoma with a population of over 51,000. Named after President James A. Garfield, the county covers a substantial area of farmland, oil fields, and communities that were established during the 1893 Cherokee Outlet land opening.</p>
      <p style="color: var(--slate-600); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 14px;">In addition to Enid, Garfield County includes the communities of Covington, Drummond, Lahoma, Waukomis, Hunter, Garber, Kremlin, Carrier, Hillsdale, Fairmont, Douglas, Breckinridge, and North Enid. Enid serves as the commercial hub of northwest Oklahoma and is home to Vance Air Force Base, a major Air Force pilot training installation. Whether the arrest occurs during a traffic stop on US-81, at an Enid business, or anywhere within the Garfield County Sheriff's jurisdiction, Angel Bail Bonds can help secure a fast release.</p>

      <h3 style="color: var(--navy); font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px;">How Far Is Garfield County from Stillwater?</h3>
